#  Bone Fracture Detection using ResNet50

A Deep Learning based Bone Fracture Detection System that analyzes X-ray images and predicts whether a bone is fractured or normal. The project utilizes Transfer Learning with ResNet50 and the MURA (Musculoskeletal Radiographs) dataset for medical image classification.

---

##  Project Overview

Bone fracture diagnosis traditionally relies on manual examination of X-ray images by medical professionals. This project aims to assist the diagnostic process using Deep Learning and Computer Vision techniques.

The system performs:

- Bone Type Classification
- Fracture Detection
- Medical Image Analysis
- GUI-Based Prediction System

The model is trained using musculoskeletal X-ray images and leverages Transfer Learning to improve prediction performance.

---

##  Features

- Fracture Detection from X-ray Images
- ResNet50 Transfer Learning
- Bone Type Classification
- GUI-Based Application
- Training and Prediction Modules
- Performance Visualization using Accuracy & Loss Graphs
- Medical Image Classification

---

##  Model Architecture

This project uses **ResNet50**, a pre-trained Convolutional Neural Network (CNN), for image classification tasks.

### Why ResNet50?

- Deep Architecture (50 Layers)
- Transfer Learning Support
- High Classification Accuracy
- Reduced Training Time
- Strong Performance on Medical Imaging Tasks

---

##  Dataset

The project uses the **MURA (Musculoskeletal Radiographs) Dataset** developed by Stanford University.

### Dataset Statistics

| Bone Part | Normal | Fractured | Total |
|------------|----------|-----------|--------|
| Elbow | 3160 | 2236 | 5396 |
| Hand | 4330 | 1673 | 6003 |
| Shoulder | 4496 | 4440 | 8936 |

**Total Images:** 20,335+

### Dataset Source

https://stanfordmlgroup.github.io/competitions/mura/

> Note: The dataset is not included in this repository due to its large size.

